	abstract = {This paper presents an automatic global design method based on enhanced particle swarm optimization-genetic algorithm (PSO-GA) for terahertz (THz) frequency multiplier circuit design. The proposed approach establishes a systematic optimization framework that integrates PSO's global search capability with GA's local optimization features. The enhanced hybrid algorithm incorporates elite pool mechanisms and dynamic population updates to improve solution quality for complex high-dimensional problems. A performance-oriented optimization process expands the design space by incorporating both continuous and discrete structural dimensions. A weighted objective function with penalty terms handles multiple performance indicators and engineering constraints. Validation through a 170260 GHz wideband frequency multiplier design demonstrates superior performance in return loss, efficiency, and bandwidth.  © 2025 IEEE.},
	type = {Conference paper},
	publication_stage = {Final},
