	doi = {10.1145/3795154.3795155},
	url = {https://www.scopus.com/pages/publications/105036517446?origin=resultslist},
	abstract = {Landslide disaster of mine dump seriously threatens mine safety production and ecological environment. Aiming at the shortcomings of traditional prediction methods such as poor adaptability and insufficient nonlinear modeling ability under complex geological conditions, an intelligent predictive control strategy based on particle swarm optimization (PSO) and Transformer is proposed in this paper. By integrating multi-source heterogeneous monitoring data of a mine, a high-dimensional time series dataset covering geological parameters, meteorological factors and operation indicators is constructed. PSO algorithm is used to optimize the hidden layer dimensions and attention heads of Transformer model globally. The experimental results show that the prediction accuracy of PSO-Transformer model is significantly improved compared with traditional ARIMA, SVR and standard Transformer. The root mean square error (RMSE) of PSO-Transformer model is reduced to 0.051, the coefficient of determination (R<sup>2</sup>) is 0.938, and the training time is reduced by 32.3% compared with genetic algorithm optimization model. Based on the prediction results, the dynamic early warning system provides an intelligent solution with both prediction accuracy and engineering feasibility for the prevention and control of dump stability. © 2025 Copyright held by the owner/author(s).},
