	abstract = {Bio-inspired computation is a field of study that connects together numerous subfields of connectionism (neural network), social behavior, emergence field of artificial intelligence and machine learning algorithms for complex problem optimization. Bio-inspired computation is motivated by nature and over the last few years, it has encouraged numerous advance algorithms and set of computational tools for dealing with complex combinatorial optimization problems. Black Hole is a new bio-inspired metaheuristic approach based on observable fact of black hole phenomena. It is a population based algorithmic approach like genetic algorithm (GAs), ant colony optimization (ACO) algorithm, particle swarm optimization (PSO), firefly and other bio-inspired computation algorithms. The objective of this book chapter is to provide a comprehensive study of black hole approach and its applications in different research fields like data clustering problem, image processing, data mining, computer vision, science and engineering. This chapter provides with the stepping stone for future researches to unveil how metaheuristic and bio-inspired commutating algorithms can improve the solutions of hard or complex problem of optimization. © Springer International Publishing Switzerland 2015},
